Access Control

Access Control
Access Control cables contain multiple cables each designed for a specific application. These applications
include: card readers, door contacts, REX (request exit), and locking power.
Although each cable has a separate application and cable requirements, they are installed in the same vicinity.
Access Control cables are grouped together to make their installation easier. There are two main methods of
grouping the cables together: applying an overall jacket or applying a substrate between the cables to “stick”
them together (Banana Peel®). Jacketed versions (ex: AFJ) are generally larger than the Banana Peel
versions (ex: AFS) and are more difficult to install since the jacket needs to be removed.
The listed Access Control cables have four different cables grouped together. Each cable ranges from #16 to
#22 AWG and has 16 to 18 conductors. Insulation material is Flamarrest® PVC. Foil shields with drain wires
are used when necessary and the jackets/substrates are Flamarrest® PVC.
